    "UIName": "Shadow Wolf",
    "Id": "chassisdef_shadow_wolf_SDW-12",
    "Name": "Shadow Wolf",
    "Details": "The Shadow Wolf SDW-12 is a 20-ton stealth recon BattleMech produced by Maltex Corporation beginning in 3068, built around Stealth Armor powered by a left-torso Guardian ECM Suite to mask its approach. Three Small Lasers and two Streak SRM 2s spread across the head, center torso, and right torso provide a close-range punch disproportionate to its weight class. A head-mounted TAG laser designates targets for allied artillery support, extending the mech's battlefield impact well beyond its own weapons.\n\n<b><color=#e62e00>Quirk: Improved Sensors</color></b>\n\n<b><color=#e62e00>Drop Cost Multiplier: 0.97</color></b>",
    "Icon": "uixTxrIcon_shadowwolf"
  },
  "VariantName": "SDW-12",
  "ChassisTags": {
    "items": [
      "mr-resize-0.51-0.56-0.54"
    ],
    "tagSetSourceFile": ""
  },
  "StockRole": "Scout",
  "YangsThoughts": "The Shadow Wolf has one of the more chaotic production histories you will find, with the Errai factory changing hands between the AFFS, the Combine, and the Word of Blake in the space of a few years before eventually landing with the Republic of the Sphere. Despite all that upheaval, the design kept getting built, which tells you the demand was real. Stealth Armor combined with TAG on a frame this fast makes it genuinely dangerous to anything operating without artillery cover, because it can call fire down on targets that never even knew it was there.",
